item.title: sdwdate cant fetch timing
item.dc:creator: Patrick
item.description:
TNT_BOM_BOM:

sudo sdwdate

It usually runs as user/group sdwdate.

github.com

Whonix/sdwdate/blob/master/lib/systemd/system/sdwdate.service#L21

    5.

  21. CapabilityBoundingSet=CAP_SYS_TIME
    22.

Running as root might break sdwdate. (Status files might be owned by root so the systemd unit file running as user could no longer write to it.)

Read full topic

item.title: sdwdate cant fetch timing
item.dc:creator: Patrick_mobile
item.description:
Don’t interrupt. Just wait.

Also it’s not supposed to be run manually. Run through systemctl or sdwdate-gui.
